                <h2>Practice makes...really good!</h2>
                <p>Doing "field work" will strengthen your arm, develop muscle memory, improve your form, and help you
                    develop a sense of what discs you need for certain situations out on the course.</p>
                <p>Practicing with the various disc types and developing your shot-shapes will help you drop strokes off
                    your score.</p>
                <p>Practice, practice, practice.</p>
